:"Isaiah","bookAbbrev":"isaiah","chapter":64,"verse":5,"text":"and we are all become as unclean, and all our righteousness as a filthy rag: and we have fallen as leaves because of our iniquities; thus the wind shall carry us .","searchKeywords":["and","are","all","become","unclean","our","righteousness","filthy","rag","have","fallen","leaves","because","iniquities","thus","the","wind","shall","carry"]},{"verseId":"brenton_isaiah_64_6","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":45,"bookName":"Isaiah","bookAbbrev":"isaiah","chapter":64,"verse":6,"text":"And there is none that calls upon thy name, or that remembers to take hold on thee: for thou hast turned thy face away from us, and hast delivered us up because of our sins.","searchKeywords":["and","there","none","that","calls","upon","thy","name","remembers","take","hold","thee","for","thou","hast","turned","face","away","from","delivered","because","our","sins"]},{"verseId":"brenton_isaiah_64_7","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":45,"bookName":"Isaiah","bookAbbrev":"isaiah","chapter":64,"verse":7,"text":"And now, O Lord, thou art our Father, and we are clay, all the work of thine hands.","searchKeywords":["and","now","lord","thou","art","our","father","are","clay","all","the","work","thine","hands"]},{"verseId":"brenton_isaiah_64_8","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":45,"bookName":"Isaiah","bookAbbrev":"isaiah","chapter":64,"verse":8,"text":"Be not very wroth with us, and remember not our sins for ever; but now look on , for we are all thy people.","searchKeywords":["not","very","wroth","with","and","remember","our","sins","for","ever","but","now","look","are","all","thy","people"]},{"verseId":"brenton_isaiah_64_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":45,"bookName":"Isaiah","bookAbbrev":"isaiah","chapter":64,"verse":9,"text":"The city of thy holiness has become desolate, Sion has become as a wilderness, Jerusalem a curse.","searchKeywords":["the",